This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques for road detection in autonomous driving, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach that involves siamesed fully convolutional networks (FCNs) and location priors, which are both common techniques in the ML sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of structured contours, which could potentially place it in the robotics (RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves deep learning techniques, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (AI) sub-category, and it discusses the use of prior knowledge, which could place it in the cryptography and security (CR) sub-category.
